commit.message: More aggressive location stripping. Ref #74.

Add get_locals kw-only argument to pickle_traceback, Frame and Traceback to allow customization of locals extraction. Fixes #41. Closes #66. Closes #67.
Disable granular error positions (pep657) since those don't survive a tblib roundtrip anyway. In other words tblib doesn't support fine grained error locations, for now...
Add some extra assertions to make sure the roundtrip produces the same traceback text.
Update skel. Drop EOL python 3.7 and add 3.12 in the test grid.
Fix remaining error manually
Run linter
bump version; test more stuff in pre-3.11
Simpler design that merges the pickle/unpickle functions
Add support for various Python 3.11 things

Remove redundant wheel dep from pyproject.toml

Remove the redundant `wheel` dependency, as it is added by the backend
automatically.  Listing it explicitly in the documentation was
a historical mistake and has been fixed since, see:
https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/commit/f7d30a9529378cf69054b5176249e5457aaf640a
